I find these statements odd.  Most successful pickup raids I've been on have done things with small numbers (usually 15-30) and a much higher (by necessity) emphasis on organization and tactics. <br>
<br>
Where as when I've seen a guild doing the same event, they would just bring the whole guild (usually about twice the people) and be done in like 30 minutes.<br>
<br>
Am I out of touch with today's pickup raids?<br>
<br>
(Don't take this to mean a pickup raid at LDoN would be a good idea.  It is simply quite hard for pre-elemental/VT players to do even the easiest of LDoN raids, despite the loot quality being what they'd go for.)<br>
