I would love to revamp LDoN raids.  There's plenty of good content there that's going unused because it's too unrewarding and too inconvenient.<br>
<br>
For starters, I'd want to switch LDoN raids over to the expedition system.  This would make it possible to swap in new members on the fly and allow us to scale the retry timer based on progress instead of giving a guaranteed 5-day lockout just for starting an instance.  Like Llanmal said, we'd also want to have loot dropping at each boss encounter instead of only at the end.  On top of all that, the loot rewards themselves could use a revamp.  Far too many of the current drops are augmentations that players capable of completing the raids have little use for.<br>
<br>
There's the small matter of how to supply adventure points at the end of the raid, (obviously, the expedition system does not support that), but I don't think the raids were ever considered an efficient way to score points anyway - it was all for the drops.  Single group LDoNs will always be more efficient than raiding for 2-3 hours.<br>
<br>
Current projects are keeping us occupied at the moment, but this is something I'd love to look into when we have more time.<br>
<br>
-Prathun <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mearisthecowslayer>Mearis The Cowslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 138<br> <font color=#330000>(7/1/04 6:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19550.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fix LDoN raids already</span><hr size=1> That's awesome Prathum <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
