<br>
First of all upping the limit to 54 would remove a lot of the risk, for those 3 way raids its still an extra group each way, and it would match the target group for hopefully what will continue past GOD.  Maybe *gasp* they could keep that number for everything until they shut down EQ(single group stuff aside).<br>
<br>
Deathcount = gone, removes all incentives to even attempt to learn LDON raids.<br>
<br>
Entry system = reworked to function like GOD trials, raid leader can zone out and then invite people to the raid, if people stay in the zone for more than 1 minute with no raid invite they get ported out.<br>
<br>
Lockout timer = down to 3 days maximum if not removed entirely.  Both are probably functionally equivalent.<br>
<br>
Given the time that I did this pickup raid was just when LDON came out so I might not entirely remember the abilities of what mobs I did see, but:<br>
<br>
The mob runs the hell away when you cast on it mobs were not fun, if there was 1 or 2 rooms like that ok, but no more than 6 or 8 of these per mission.<br>
<br>
I seem to remember there being some trash mobs with AE RAMPAGE, if that is so then set that to regular rampage.  Trash mobs with AE rampage is rediculous.<br>
<br>
I only did one of these btw, so the other really rediculous stuff like that from the other ones its probably just best to cut down on that stuff too.<br>
<br>
Now then - Risk vs Reward - All of the above lowers the risk of the raids quite a lot when taken together, still imho some changes do need to be made here.<br>
<br>
First of all, the end boss stays as is.<br>
<br>
Secondly, any/all mini bosses currently in the raids start dropping loot, namely loot that is ~85% as good as the end boss loot.<br>
<br>
Thirdly, Sprinkle random named throughout the dungeon that have nothing to do with the actual winning of the mission (like in single group missions) which have loot ~60% of the end boss loot.<br>
<br>
Fourthly, make a random rare loot list and have it drop off the trash mobs, set it to where either 1 or 2 will drop off the the combined total of every trash mob in the zone.  There should never be 0, nor should there ever be 3+.  <br>
<br>
Impressario Raiddinn the Beatdropper<br>
